<p>Using <code>auto</code> when the type that would be deduced is a pointer type can cause confusion. It is much better to specify the pointer part
outside of <code>auto</code>.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
auto item = new Item(); // Noncompliant
</pre>
<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>
<pre>
auto* item = new Item();
</pre>